properties.description: Posted by Alexkenefick  4PM to 10 PM, December 16. Several fire rings at the beach. The only legal beach bonfire in Los Angeles County. Screaming Jets taking off throught the fog from LAX. A perfect post-nuclear holiday location. BYO-WYWTH (Bring Your Own Whatever You Want To Have) Possible activities: Large approximation of menorah with each fire ring signifying a candle socket and a flame-thrower or modified leaf -blower signifying a shamus. Looking forward to winter Solstice (next week--YES!) Beach Badmitton? Beach Blanket Twister? Alcoholic Beverage Consumption?
